resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These incidents come just hours before the Olympic torch relay concludes and the opening ceremony begins, with more than320,000 spectators expectedto attend along the River Seine.\", \"from\": 3391, \"to\": 3570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3558, \"end\": 3569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony will go ahead as planned, a Paris 2024 spokesperson told CNN, and organizers have \\\"no concerns from their side in light of the overnight events on the train network.\\\"\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3620, \"end\": 3630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.331477882630576e-23, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3649, \"end\": 3652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 4.913451947906423e-12, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yves Herman/Reuters  The French Minister of Sports and the Olympic and Paralympic Games, Am\\u00e9lie Oud\\u00e9a-Castera said the disruption to the train lines are \\\"a sort of coordinated sabotage.\\\"\", \"from\": 3760, \"to\": 3946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3765, \"end\": 3771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikolaus_Herman\", \"score\": 0.9984726963953968, \"rank\": 0.0013297877199036987, \"text\": \"Herman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikolaus_Herman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikolaus_Herman\"}, {\"begin\": 3772, \"end\": 3779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3350717762431895e-20, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 3849, \"end\": 3855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Am\\u00e9lie\", \"score\": 0.9436703648892786, \"rank\": 0.024506514014996705, \"text\": \"Am\\u00e9lie\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Am\\u00e9lie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Am\\u00e9lie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking BFMTV, Oud\\u00e9a-Castera condemned the attacks in the \\\"strongest possible terms,\\\" and said it is \\\"truly appalling.\\\"\", \"from\": 3948, \"to\": 4068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We will assess the impacts on travelers, athletes, and ensure the proper transport of all delegations to the competition sites,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other French officials echoed her description of the attacks being intentional.\", \"from\": 4211, \"to\": 4290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4217, \"end\": 4223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999989484254983, \"rank\": 9.110684516936634e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Outgoing French transport minister Patrice Vergriete and Valerie Pecresse, head of the \\u00cele-de-France region, in which Paris lies, said on Friday that \\\"all elements\\\" pointed towards it being a \\\"deliberate attack.\\\"\", \"from\": 4291, \"to\": 4503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4300, \"end\": 4306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franc